  "prompt": "How did Harley Quinn skin become white?",
  "response": "Harley Quinn's signature white skin is primarily attributed to her portrayal in various forms of media, particularly the \"Batman: The Animated Series\" where her character was introduced. In this show, her skin color is visually striking, giving her a clown-like appearance that aligns with her jester theme. \n\nIn the comics, her transformation into a character with white skin is not as straightforward. Over the years, different interpretations and retellings of her origin story have varied. One common explanation is that after her psychological transformation into Harley Quinn, she uses makeup to create her pale complexion, similar to the Joker. In some versions, especially after being exposed to various chemicals alongside the Joker, she acquires a more permanently pale skin tone.\n\nIn essence, Harley Quinn's white skin serves as an iconic aspect of her visual identity, distinguishing her from other characters and emphasizing her connection to the Joker's chaotic, clown-like aesthetic.",
